<Page x:Class="AsynAwaitExamples.Steps.Step24_Timeouts"
      xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
      xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
      xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:AsynAwaitExamples.ViewModels"
      Title="Step 24 - Timeouts">
    <Page.DataContext>
        <vm:Step24ViewModel/>
    </Page.DataContext>
    <ScrollViewer VerticalScrollBarVisibility="Auto">
        <StackPanel Margin="10">
            <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource HeaderStyle}" 
                       Text="Step 24: Timeouts (CancelAfter &amp; Task.WaitAsync)"/>

            <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource ExplanationStyle}" xml:space="preserve">TIMEOUTS: Setting time limits on async operations.

Two approaches:
1. CancelAfter: Automatically cancels a CancellationToken after a duration.
   The method cooperatively stops when it checks the token.
   Best when the method accepts CancellationToken.

2. Task.WaitAsync(timeout): Wraps any task with a timeout. If it takes too
   long, throws TimeoutException. Does NOT cancel the underlying task!
   Best when you don't control the method's internals.

PRODUCTION PATTERN: Use both together for robustness.
   CancelAfter asks the method to stop (cooperative).
   WaitAsync is a safety net if the method ignores cancellation.</TextBlock>

            <Button Style="{StaticResource ActionButton}"
                    Content="?? CancelAfter (cooperative cancellation)"
                    Command="{Binding CancelAfterDemoCommand}"
                    IsEnabled="{Binding IsRunning, Converter={StaticResource InvertBoolConverter}}"/>
            <Button Style="{StaticResource ActionButton}"
                    Content="? Task.WaitAsync (timeout without cancellation)"
                    Command="{Binding WaitAsyncDemoCommand}"
                    IsEnabled="{Binding IsRunning, Converter={StaticResource InvertBoolConverter}}"/>
            <Button Style="{StaticResource ActionButton}"
                    Content="?? Combined: CancelAfter + WaitAsync"
                    Command="{Binding CombinedDemoCommand}"
                    IsEnabled="{Binding IsRunning, Converter={StaticResource InvertBoolConverter}}"/>
            <Button Style="{StaticResource ActionButton}"
                    Content="? Timeout success (finishes in time)"
                    Command="{Binding SuccessfulTimeoutCommand}"
                    IsEnabled="{Binding IsRunning, Converter={StaticResource InvertBoolConverter}}"/>

            <TextBox Style="{StaticResource OutputStyle}" Height="280"
                     Text="{Binding OutputText, Mode=OneWay}"/>
        </StackPanel>
    </ScrollViewer>
</Page>
